20 SECTION 3. IC 27-7-6-6, AS AMENDED BY P.L.196-2021,
21 SECTION 36, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
22 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. (a) An insurer shall not fail to renew a policy
23 unless it mails to the named insured, at the address shown in the policy,
24 at least twenty (20) sixty (60) days advance notice of its intention not
25 to renew the policy.
26 (b) If a policy was procured by an independent insurance producer
27 duly licensed by the state of Indiana, a notice of intent not to renew the
28 policy shall be mailed to the independent insurance producer at least
29 ten (10) days prior to the mailing of the notice of intention not to renew
30 to the named insured under subsection (a), unless such notice of intent
31 is or has been waived in writing by the independent insurance
32 producer.
33 (c) This section does not apply:
34 (1) if the insurer has manifested its willingness to renew; or
35 (2) in case of nonpayment of premium.
36 However, notwithstanding the failure of an insurer to comply with this
37 section, the policy shall terminate on the effective date of any other
38 insurance policy with respect to any automobile designated in both
39 policies.
40 (d) A notice of intention not to renew is not required under this
41 section if:
42 (1) the insured is transferred from an insurer to an affiliate of the
