1 coverage under a master policy for:
2 (1) the land on which the condominium is located;
3 (2) swimming pools and other recreational facilities; or
4 (3) any other parts of the condominium existing for common
5 use.
6 SECTION 7. IC 27-19-3-1.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
7 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
8 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. The commissioner shall have the authority to do
9 the following:
10 (1) Establish any program, promulgate any rule, policy,
11 guideline, or plan, or change any program, rule, policy, or
12 guideline to:
13 (A) implement;
14 (B) establish;
15 (C) create;
16 (D) administer; or
17 (E) otherwise operate;
18 a health benefit exchange.
19 (2) Apply for, accept, or expend federal money related to the
20 creation, implementation, or operation of a health benefit
21 exchange.
22 (3) Establish any advisory board or committee that the
23 commissioner deems necessary to provide recommendations
24 on the creation, implementation, or operation of a health
25 benefit exchange.
